The evidence with the title 'How quickly are health insurance premiums rising? | PBS NewsHour ' says Aug 21, 2013  ... Health insurance premiums have risen 196 percent since 1999 , with worker contributions growing 182 percent.  ... Analysts say premium increases are cyclical , with periods of rapid increases, such as the double-digit hikes that marked the late 1980s and the early 2000s, followed by periods of slower  ... 
